value.title: AOC says she disagrees with Biden's 'optimistic' view of GOP
value.excerpt: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez said she disagrees with President-elect Biden on his “optimistic” view of the GOP.

value.title: Biden: We'll 'manage the hell' out of feds' COVID response
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is pledging to boost supplies of coronavirus vaccine and set up new vaccination sites to meet his goal of 100 million shots in 100 days

value.title: Harold Bornstein, Trump's former doctor who said he'd be the 'healthiest' president of all time, dies at 73
value.excerpt: Bornstein rose to global fame after he declared Trump "the healthiest individual ever elected to the presidency." But Trump still cast him aside.

value.title: 'It's not their party any more': Trump leaves Republicans deeply fractured
value.excerpt: The president has ignited a civil war in his own party, creating bitter divides that will be felt for years to come

value.title: Key witness in first Trump impeachment says 'we're not out of the woods yet' after January 6 Capitol attack
value.excerpt: "Just because it didn't have a high likelihood of succeeding in a classic coup fashion doesn't mean it wasn't an attempt," Fiona Hill says.

value.title: Biden: Science will be at `forefront' of his administration
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden says “science will always be at the forefront of my administration,” and he's elevating the post of science adviser to Cabinet level, a White House first

value.title: Trump's regulators OK 'partnership' that could squeeze air passengers in D.C. and NYC
value.excerpt: OK'd on Elaine Chao's final day as transportation secretary — is generating complaints it will harm competition and raise fares.

value.title: Trump finishes with worst first term approval rating ever
value.excerpt: Poll of the week: A new Quinnipiac University poll finds that President Donald Trump's approval rating stands at 33%, while his disapproval is at 60%.

value.title: Census battle ends as Trump administration gives up on excluding undocumented from apportionment
value.excerpt: A high-stakes six-month battle over who should be counted for representation in Congress ended quietly in a judge’s chamber Friday night when the Trump administration agreed not to release any population numbers from the 2020 Census for congressional apportionment or redistricting before the president leaves office.

value.title: Capitol rioters came within a minute of reaching Pence, report says
value.excerpt: The mob that invaded the Capitol on Jan. 6 nearly reached the Senate floor only about a minute after Vice President Mike Pence left the chamber, The Washington Post reported. A Secret Service ...

value.title: Trump trial pending, McConnell calls it ‘vote of conscience’
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump’s impeachment trial is likely to start after Joe Biden’s inauguration, and the Republican leader, Mitch McConnell, is telling senators their decision on whether to convict the outgoing president over the Capitol riot will be a “vote of conscience.

value.title: Pence speaks at memorial service for Yeager in West Virginia
value.excerpt: Retired Air Force Brig. Gen. Chuck Yeager was remembered at a memorial service Friday as a hero, legend and friend who would go out of his way to help others.

value.title: Police: Man charged after displaying ‘KILL BIDEN’ sign
value.excerpt: A Virginia man has been arrested for having a “KILL BIDEN” sign. WWBT in Richmond reported Thursday that Kenneth Kraig Thomas of Goochland County was arrested and is facing a charge of threatening a person in writing.

value.title: Capitol riots: What are far-right Trump supporters saying?
value.excerpt: Members of the extreme right are searching for new online homes, amid paranoia that they are being ‘set up’ by the authorities.

value.title: Trump receives Morocco's highest award for Middle East work: official
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump on Friday received Morocco's highest award for his work in advancing a normalization deal between Israel and Morocco, a senior administration official told Reuters.

value.title: Proud Boys Intended To Kill Mike Pence and Nancy Pelosi, FBI Witness Says
value.excerpt: A group allegedly involved in the violent breach of the U.S. Capitol last week, including at least one self-proclaimed member of the Proud Boys, said that "they would have killed [Vice President] Mike Pence if given the chance,

value.title: 'What the hell is wrong with them?': Biden rips Republicans for refusing to don masks during siege
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is taking aim at some Republican members of Congress who refused to wear masks while huddling in secure rooms last week during the storming of the Capitol.

value.title: FBI agent in Trump-Russia's request for 'validation' of Steele reporting denied, left Crossfire Hurricane
value.excerpt: An agent involved in the FBI’s original Trump-Russia case left the Crossfire Hurricane team amid a “professional disagreement” with Bill Priestap, after the former assistant director of counterintelligence denied his request for an “enhanced validation review” of Christopher Steele’s reporting.

value.title: Manhattan DA expands criminal investigation into Trump Organization finances to include family compound in Westchester County
value.excerpt: The Manhattan district attorney's office has expanded its criminal investigation into the Trump Organization's finances to include the family's compound in Westchester County, according to lawyers and people familiar with the investigation.

value.title: Trump plans to depart Washington Inauguration Day morning, while Pence, Harris speak
value.excerpt: President Trump plans to make the unprecedented move to depart the White House next Wednesday morning, just before President-elect Joe Biden's inauguration.

value.title: Despite Trump administration promise, there appear to be no more 'reserve' 2nd vaccine doses to release
value.excerpt: Hopes of a surge in Covid-19 vaccine shipments under a new policy to release second doses held in reserve appear to be evaporating -- with the revelation that those doses have already been distributed, contrary to recent indications by the Trump administration.

value.title: Pence calls Harris while Trump continues to stew in denial
value.excerpt: One is dropping in on the White House phone operators, addressing troops at bases across the country, paying a visit to national guardsmen in place for the inauguration and speaking by phone with his successor.

value.title: Cuomo takes parting shot at Trump admin, targets 'reclamation' of SALT funds
value.excerpt: The SALT cap has been one of the bigger thorns in Cuomo's side in recent years.

value.title: VP-elect Harris compares Capitol riots to 2017 'Unite the Right' rally
value.excerpt: Vice President-Elect Kamala Harris said Thursday that last week's assault on the U.S. Capitol reminded her of the 2017 "Unite the Right" rally in Charlottesville, Va.
